doc.after: On 24 May 2011 Mubarak was ordered to stand trial on charges of premeditated murder of peaceful protesters during the 2011 Egyptian revolution and if convicted could face the death penalty The decision to try Mubarak was made days before a scheduled protest in Tahrir Square The full list of charges released by the public prosecutor was intentional murder attempted killing of some demonstrators misuse of influence deliberately wasting public funds and unlawfully making private financial gains and profits 10
